        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 3:45PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 345 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles west of Marshall, or 8 miles southwest of Hot Springs, moving
north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hot Springs, Max Patch, and Spring Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
